links.title: Eli Lilly requests emergency approval for its Covid-19 antibody treatment
links.description: Drugmaker Eli Lilly said Wednesday that it has requested an emergency use authorization from the Food and Drug Administration for its Covid-19 monoclonal antibody treatment. Lilly's medication is similar to the Regeneron antibody treatment President Donald Trump received after his Covid-19 diagnosis. Regeneron has not yet applied for such an authorization.

$LLY Eli Lilly CEO says still 'thinking about' price for COVID-19 antibody drug 13:46 LLY Eli Lilly CEO David Ricks said in an interview on CNBC that setting the price of the company's antibody drug to treat COVID-19 is an "important issue" that the company is still "thinking about," but he added that the company is working to make sure it sets the price at a level to make the drug available to those who need it. As previously reported this morning, Eli Lilly has now submitted an initial request for EUA for LY-CoV555 monotherapy in higher-risk patients who have been recently diagnosed with mild-to-moderate COVID-19 and expects to submit a subsequent request for EUA for combination therapy in November, pending clinical trial enrollment, once additional safety data accumulate and sufficient supply is manufactured.
